  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Electrid activity of the basal ganglia will be recorded with an implantable deep brain
      stimulation device (supplied by Medtronic Inc).

      Study hypothesis is that these activities differ according to what the patient does, i.e. are
      different during gait and speech.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
